  "instructions": [
    "In a small bowl, whisk together fish sauce, lime juice, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, garlic, black pepper, and salt.",
    "Add the mixture to a large ziplock bag with the pork shoulder and massage to coat.",
    "Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.",
    "Preheat a charcoal or gas grill to medium-high heat.",
    "Remove the pork from the marinade and cook for 5-7 minutes per side, or until cooked through.",
    "Transfer the pork to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Thinly slice the pork against the grain.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together rice vinegar, ginger, and sesame oil.",
    "Add the sliced pork to the bowl and toss to coat.",
    "Assemble the rolls by placing a piece of pork, some cucumber, mint leaves, and lettuce leaves onto a rice noodle.",
    "Drizzle with the dressing and sprinkle with sesame seeds.",
    "Serve immediately."
  ],
